p thresholds</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2a5489cf4dbc"><strong>Rapid Recovery: </strong>(Pending PS T=
eam engagement)</p>
<p local-id=3D"4c25982f489d">Ingenium Gold RRP delivered (Balaji Ravi / Sen=
thil Kumar Jaganathan) to the mandatory standard template =E2=80=94 covers =
a full restart sequence (WAS =E2=86=92 CICS =E2=86=92 DB) and a batch-slown=
ess workaround, with RTO/RPO Primary 2h/2h and DR 4h/4h. Kanagaraj's restar=
t runbooks have been integrated as the baseline. A mandatory server-restart=
 authorization decision matrix is now required in every RRP, driven by the =
ambiguity surfaced during INC08624117. AI-assisted RRP drafting workflow bu=
ilt for PS team; PS team still needs to assign authors per application.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f36d92c59236">
<li local-id=3D"029f33be-6790-426a-b74f-f5df6c6461a3">
<p local-id=3D"1869991c2b0b">DK and Balaj do Quality control on the incomin=
g draft documentation</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a64e988f-c3cc-4b6f-ad69-4ec4a7789830">
<li local-id=3D"f680a844-875b-408f-b9bf-e009751d2fff">
<p local-id=3D"da3f5e3fa5f4">Jonan - Sequence out the responses</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f1893751d508"><strong>Patching: </strong>(Pending PS Team en=
gagement)</p>
<p local-id=3D"60a14d4e148f">Standardization and weekday patch registration=
 meetings continue; the first application weekday onboarding is being confi=
rmed. Weekday patching for non-Gold, non-batch apps/servers remains the pat=
h for reducing weekend workload (Karen, Sreekanth, Kanaraj).&nbsp; <strong>=
RISK</strong>: Team repeats the same questions every week and don't have th=
e skill to query CMDB or Service Now to establish standardized changes for =
patching.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6643f80150d0"><strong>Employee XP Dashboard</strong>:</p>
<p local-id=3D"b2d876b1a88d">David got feedback from Ito-san on <em>Employe=
e XP</em>, <em>Business Capability</em>, and <em>Branch monitoring </em>das=
hboards. He would like to have external App health check reports for IT-sav=
vy business team members.&nbsp; Enhancements will be made in parallel based=
 on Dev XP Dashboard improvements</p>
<p local-id=3D"6b3718397b1c"><strong>Dev XP Dashboard</strong>:</p>
<p local-id=3D"fb40e43d3145">In beta with the AQA group. Alerting tightened=
 to actionable signals only: push for real-time action, dashboard for the f=
ull data surface across all environments, and Rae's daily summary email for=
 one-page health. Sleeping-system false alerts being tuned out, active hour=
s (9am-9pm JST) set; Focus on process monitoring now.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5dbf417ccbc0"><strong>CMDB Mapping:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"f153e6bc8e9c">Yegor continues cleaning up app mapping</p>
<p local-id=3D"49a13202bb8b"><strong>GOCC Transition: </strong>(Pending PS =
Team engagement)</p>
<p local-id=3D"1097af3f1e04">GOCC Yam is moving to a different team and han=
ding over to Rae for remaining applications. <strong>PS Team Risk</strong>&=
nbsp;related to responsiveness during contract transition.</p>
<p local-id=3D"5816a5396789"></p>
<p local-id=3D"b098a506e878"><strong><u>Additional related work</u></strong=
></p>
<p local-id=3D"b460f9b161a4"><strong>Branch / JPE-JPW:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"4cb162870531">Non-prod VNet setup complete (post-provisionin=
